description:
&lt;p&gt;Theatre Practitioners - Anaesthetics&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for Band 5 Theatre Practitioners to join our dynamic, friendly and forward thinking team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bolton NHS Foundation Trust is committed to being the best in our class of organisations. We offer a culture that supports our staff and helps them to be the best that they can be and enables them to achieve better care to patients. All staff work to a set of five core values:-&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Vision&lt;br /&gt;• Openness&lt;br /&gt;• Integrity&lt;br /&gt;• Compassion&lt;br /&gt;• Excellence&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Royal Bolton Hospital is easily accessible from the M61 and has good public transport links.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are currently recruiting qualified operating department practitioners and nurses to work in our theatre department which covers a wide range of specialities including general surgery, trauma and elective orthopaedics, oncoplastics, breast, gynaecology, obstetrics, ENT and oral maxillofacial surgery. &lt;br /&gt;Whether you are just setting out on your career or are experienced with transferable skills we would like to talk to you about the opportunities to join us and care for our patients at a vulnerable time in their lives and to provide optimised patient outcomes every time. In return for your commitment, enthusiasm and dedication we will provide you with the technical skills and provide one to one support from our dedicated Practice Educator and Clinical Skills Facilitator. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As an organisation we are committed to placing the patient at the heart of everything we do and in the provision of safe, effective patient care that acknowledges and ensures dignity. With this in mind we are seeking to recruit staff who share the organisation’s values and beliefs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be highly motivated with a can do attitude and will join an innovative and pro-active team to provide safe, clean and personal care using evidence based practice. You will be a registered nurse with current NMC registration, a qualified Operating Department Practitioner with HCPC registration, a Student Nurse or Student ODP.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post-holder will be expected to be flexible to respond to change and organisational needs. There is a requirement to work flexible hours over the 24 hour day, including weekends and on call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kristopher booth- Team manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: kristopher.booth2@boltonft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01204 390390 ext ext 144858&lt;/p&gt;
